Source: libdiscid
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Tux Mason <tuxmason@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), gcc-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: http://musicbrainz.org/doc/libdiscid

Package: libdiscid
Section: libs
Architecture: ARCH
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: A Library for creating MusicBrainz DiscIDs
 This package provides libdiscid, a shared library which
 contains routines for creating MusicBrainz DiscIDs from 
 audio CDs. 
 .
 It reads a CD's table of contents (TOC) and generates an 
 identifier which can be used to lookup the CD at MusicBrainz 
 (http://musicbrainz.org). Additionally, it provides a 
 submission URL for adding the DiscID to the database.

Package: libdiscid-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: ARCH
Priority: optional
Depends: libdiscid (= ${binary:Version}), gcc-dev 
Description: libdiscid headers and static library
 This package provides the libdiscid static library, 
 pkgconfig data and header files required to develop
 applications which use libdiscid API functions.
